Documentation.name: SAF
Documentation.notes: System Architecture Framework (SAF) is an architecture framework to define architectures for complex cyber-physical systems. The profile implements the SAF concept model defined by INCOSE (GfSE as German Chapter) and provides useful SysML-based stereotypes, diagram types and linking rules.

RootTable.Filter: select distinct LogElem.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", LogElem.name as "Logical Element", PhyItem.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", PhyItem.name as "Physical Item" -- find all Logical Elements with an Logical Role instance which has an allocate connection from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst, t_object LogElem, t_object PhyItem where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and c.end_object_id = Phy_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = LogElem.ea_guid and Phy_Inst.pdata1 = PhyItem.ea_guid and Log_Inst.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalInternalRole" and Phy_Inst.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalInternalRole" union -- find all Logical Elements w/o an instance which have no allocate connections to physical instances select o.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", o.name as "Logical Element", null, null from t_object o where o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalElement" and o.object_id not in (SELECT distinct Phy_Inst.object_id from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = Phy_Inst.ea_guid) union -- find all Physical Elements w/o an instance which have no allocate connections to logical instances select null, null, o.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", o.name as "Physical Item" from t_object o where o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalElement" and o.object_id not in (SELECT distinct Phy_Inst.object_id from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.end_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = Phy_Inst.ea_guid)

-- search for allocation chain Action - logical role - physical role and determine the classifier select distinct pi.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", pi.name as "Physical Item", act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_connector c1, t_connector c2, t_object fa, t_object lir, t_object pir, t_object act, t_object le, t_object pi where c1.stereotype = 'allocate' and c1.start_object_id = fa.object_id and c1.end_object_id = lir.object_id and fa.Classifier = act.Object_ID and lir.pdata1 = le.ea_guid and fa.Object_Type = "Action" and lir.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalInternalRole" and c2.stereotype = "allocate" and c2.start_object_id = lir.object_id and c2.end_object_id = pir.object_id and pir.pdata1 = pi.ea_guid and pir.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalInternalRole" union -- search for chain Action - activity partition - Logical Element, and allocation link between logical role - physical role and determine the classifiers select distinct pi.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", pi.name as "Physical Item", act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_object fa, t_object par, t_object act, t_object le, t_connector c, t_object lir, t_object pir, t_object pi where fa.Object_Type = "Action" and par.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and fa.parentID = par.Object_ID and fa.Classifier = act.Object_ID and par.Classifier = le.Object_ID and le.Stereotype = "SAF_LogicalElement" and c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = lir.object_id and c.end_object_id = pir.object_id and lir.pdata1 = le.ea_guid and pir.pdata1 = pi.ea_guid and lir.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalInternalRole" and pir.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalInternalRole" union -- find all functions without allocations or partitions select null, null, act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_object act where act.stereotype = "SAF_SystemPartialFunction" and act.name not in (select distinct o3.name from t_object o1, t_object o2, t_object o3, t_object o4 where o1.Object_Type = "Action" and o2.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and o1.parentID = o2.Object_ID and o1.Classifier = o3.Object_ID and o2.Classifier = o4.Object_ID) and act.name not in (SELECT distinct o2.name from t_connector c, t_object o1, t_object o2 where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = o1.object_id and o1.Classifier = o2.Object_ID) union -- find all physical items without allocated elements select o.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", o.name as "Physical Item", null, null from t_object o where o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalElement" and o.name not in (SELECT distinct o2.name from t_connector c, t_object o1, t_object o2 where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.end_object_id = o1.object_id and o1.pdata1 = o2.ea_guid)

select distinct oc.name as "Operational Capability", oc.note as "Notes", os.name as "Supporting Operational Story", op.name as "Exhibiting Operational Performer", req.name as "Refined by Stakeholder Requirement" from ((((((t_object oc -- find SAF_OperationalStory over SAF_OperationalCapabilitySupport connector left join t_connector os_supporting on oc.object_ID = os_supporting.start_object_ID and os_supporting.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapabilitySupport") left join t_object os on os_supporting.end_object_id = os.object_id and os.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalStory") -- find SAF_OperationalPerformer over SAF_OperationalPerformerExhibit connector left join t_connector op_exhibit on oc.object_ID = op_exhibit.end_object_ID and op_exhibit.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformerExhibit") left join t_object op on op_exhibit.start_object_id = op.object_id and op.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformer") -- find SAF_StakeholderRequirements over SAF_StakeholderRequirementRefinement left join t_connector req_refinement on oc.object_ID = req_refinement.end_object_ID and req_refinement.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirementRefinement") left join t_object req on req_refinement.start_object_id = req.object_id and req.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirement") where oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability"

select distinct op.name as "Operational Process", op.note as "Notes", os.name as "Refining Operational Story", oc.name as "Enabling Operational Capability", operf.name as "Process Performed by" from ((((((t_object op -- find SAF_OperationalStory over SAF_OperationalCapabilitySupport connector left join t_connector os_refining on op.object_ID = os_refining.start_object_ID and os_refining.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcessRefinement") left join t_object os on os_refining.end_object_id = os.object_id and os.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalStory") -- find SAF_OperationalCapabilities over SAF_OperationalProcessEnabling connector left join t_connector op_enabling on op.object_ID = op_enabling.start_object_ID and op_enabling.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcessEnabling") left join t_object oc on op_enabling.end_object_id = oc.object_id and oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability") -- find SAF_OperationalPerformer over Activity Partition Classifier left join t_object ap on op.object_ID = ap.parentID and ap.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition") left join t_object operf on ap.Classifier = operf.object_id and operf.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalPerformer") where op.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalProcess"

select distinct id.value as "ID", sreq.stereotype as "Requirement Stereotype", sreq.name as "System Requirement", sreq.note as "Notes", src.stereotype as "Source Stereotype", src.name as "Source" from ((t_object sreq -- find traces left join t_connector req_src on sreq.object_id = req_src.start_object_id and (req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementRefinement" or req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementDerivation" or req_src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementFunctionalRefinement" or "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirementConstraint" )) left join t_object src on req_src.end_object_id = src.object_id and (src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemUseCase" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapability" or src.stereotype = "ProxyPort" or src.stereotype = "SAF_StakeholderRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemNonFunctionalRequirement" or src.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirement")) -- find Requirement ID if available left join t_objectproperties id on (sreq.object_id = id.object_id) -- consider only SAF_SystemRequirement, SAF_SystemNonFunctionalRequirement and SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirement where (sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement" or sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemNonFunctionalRequirement" or sreq.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunctionalRequirement") and id.Property in ('id')

select distinct Activity.stereotype as "Stereotype F", Activity.name as "Function", LogElem.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", LogElem.name as "Logical Element" from t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance, t_object Activity, t_object LogElem -- find all actions (which are not a Partial Function) below a Activity Partition where Action.Object_Type = "Action" and LE_Instance.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and Action.parentID = LE_Instance.Object_ID and Action.Classifier = Activity.Object_ID and LE_Instance.Classifier = LogElem.Object_ID and not (Activity.Stereotype = "SAF_SystemPartialFunction") union -- find all Actions which have a allocate connector to a Logical Role select distinct Activity.stereotype as "Stereotype F", Activity.name as "Function", LogElem.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", LogElem.name as "Logical Element" from t_connector c, t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance, t_object Activity, t_object LogElem where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Action.object_id and c.end_object_id = LE_Instance.object_id and Action.Classifier = Activity.Object_ID and LE_Instance.pdata1 = LogElem.ea_guid and Action.Object_Type = "Action" and LE_Instance.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalContextRole" union -- find all Activities w/o an Action instances below a Activity Partition select o.stereotype as "Stereotype F", o.name as "Function", null, null from t_object o where (o.stereotype = "SAF_ContextFunction" or o.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunction") and o.Object_ID not in (select distinct Activity.Object_ID from t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance, t_object Activity, t_object LogElem where Action.Object_Type = "Action" and LE_Instance.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and Action.parentID = LE_Instance.Object_ID and Action.Classifier = Activity.Object_ID and LE_Instance.Classifier = LogElem.Object_ID) and o.Object_ID not in (SELECT distinct LE_Instance.Object_ID from t_connector c, t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Action.object_id and Action.Classifier = LE_Instance.Object_ID) union -- find all Logical SOIs / Logical User / Logical Environment / Logical External System without Actions below a Activity Partition nor having an allocate connection select null, null, o.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", o.name as "Logical Element" from t_object o where (o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalSOI" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalUser" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalEnvironment" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalExternalSystem") and o.Object_ID not in (SELECT distinct Action.Object_ID from t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance, t_object Activity where LE_Instance.Classifier = Action.Object_ID and Activity.parentID = LE_Instance.Object_ID and Activity.Stereotype = "SAF_FunctionAction") and o.Object_ID not in (SELECT distinct LE_Instance.Object_ID from t_connector c, t_object Action, t_object LE_Instance where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.end_object_id = Action.object_id and Action.Classifier = LE_Instance.Object_ID)

select distinct LogElem.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", LogElem.name as "Logical Element", PhyItem.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", PhyItem.name as "Physical Item" -- find all Logical Elements with an Logical Role instance which has an allocate connection from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst, t_object LogElem, t_object PhyItem where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and c.end_object_id = Phy_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = LogElem.ea_guid and Phy_Inst.pdata1 = PhyItem.ea_guid and Log_Inst.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalContextRole" and Phy_Inst.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalContextRole" union -- find all Logical SOIs / Logical User / Logical External System / Logical External System w/o an instance which have no allocate connections to physical instances select o.stereotype as "Stereotype LE", o.name as "Logical Element", null, null from t_object o where (o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalSOI" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalUser" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalEnvironment" or o.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalExternalSystem") and o.object_id not in (SELECT distinct Phy_Inst.object_id from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = Phy_Inst.ea_guid) union -- find all physical systems / Physical User / Physical Environment / Physical External System w/o an instance which have no allocate connections to logical instances select null, null, o.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", o.name as "Physical Item" from t_object o where (o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalSystem" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalUser" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalExternalSystem" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalEnvironment")and o.object_id not in (SELECT distinct Phy_Inst.object_id from t_connector c, t_object Log_Inst, t_object Phy_Inst where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.end_object_id = Log_Inst.object_id and Log_Inst.pdata1 = Phy_Inst.ea_guid)

select distinct sc.name as "System Capability", sc.note as "Notes", oc.name as "Enabling Operational Capability", uc.name as "Supporting System Use Case", sp.name as "Supported By System Process", req.name as "Refined by System Requirement" from ((((((((t_object sc -- find SAF_OperationalCapability over SAF_SystemCapabilityEnabling connector left join t_connector oc_enabling on sc.object_ID = oc_enabling.start_object_id and oc_enabling.stereotype = 'SAF_SystemCapabilityEnabling') left join t_object oc on oc_enabling.end_object_id = oc.object_id and oc.stereotype = "SAF_OperationalCapability") -- find SAF_SystemUseCase over SAF_SystemCapabilitySupport connector left join t_connector uc_supporting on sc.object_ID = uc_supporting.start_object_ID and uc_supporting.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapabilitySupport") left join t_object uc on uc_supporting.end_object_id = uc.object_id and uc.stereotype = "SAF_SystemUseCase") -- find SAF_SystemProcess over SAF_SystemProcessEnabling connector left join t_connector supporting_sp on sc.object_ID = supporting_sp.end_object_id and supporting_sp.stereotype = "SAF_SystemProcessEnabling") left join t_object sp on supporting_sp.start_object_id = sp.object_id and sp.stereotype = "SAF_SystemProcess") -- find SAF_SystemRequirement over SAF_SystemRequirementRefinement left join t_connector refining_req on sc.object_id = refining_req.end_object_id and refining_req.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirementRefinement") left join t_object req on refining_req.start_object_id = req.object_id and req.stereotype = "SAF_SystemRequirement") where sc.stereotype = "SAF_SystemCapability"

-- search for allocation chain Action - logical role - physical role and determine the classifier select distinct pi.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", pi.name as "Physical Item", act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_connector c1, t_connector c2, t_object fa, t_object lir, t_object pir, t_object act, t_object le, t_object pi where c1.stereotype = 'allocate' and c1.start_object_id = fa.object_id and c1.end_object_id = lir.object_id and fa.Classifier = act.Object_ID and lir.pdata1 = le.ea_guid and fa.Object_Type = "Action" and lir.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalContextRole" and c2.stereotype = "allocate" and c2.start_object_id = lir.object_id and c2.end_object_id = pir.object_id and pir.pdata1 = pi.ea_guid and pir.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalContextRole" union -- search for chain Action - activity partition - Logical Element, and allocation link between logical role - physical role and determine the classifiers select pi.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", pi.name as "Physical Item", act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_object fa, t_object par, t_object act, t_object le, t_connector c, t_object lir, t_object pir, t_object pi where fa.Object_Type = "Action" and par.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and fa.parentID = par.Object_ID and fa.Classifier = act.Object_ID and par.Classifier = le.Object_ID and (le.Stereotype = "SAF_LogicalSOI" or le.Stereotype = "SAF_LogicalUser" or le.Stereotype = "SAF_LogicalEnvironment" or le.Stereotype = "SAF_LogicalExternalSystem") and c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = lir.object_id and c.end_object_id = pir.object_id and lir.pdata1 = le.ea_guid and pir.pdata1 = pi.ea_guid and lir.stereotype = "SAF_LogicalContextRole" and pir.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalContextRole" union -- find all functions without allocations or partitions select null, null, act.stereotype as "Stereotype F", act.name as "Function" from t_object act where (act.stereotype = "SAF_SystemFunction" or act.stereotype = "SAF_ContextFunction") and act.object_id not in (select o3.object_id from t_object o1, t_object o2, t_object o3, t_object o4 where o1.Object_Type = "Action" and o2.Object_Type = "ActivityPartition" and o1.parentID = o2.Object_ID and o1.Classifier = o3.Object_ID and o2.Classifier = o4.Object_ID) and act.object_id not in (SELECT o2.object_id from t_connector c, t_object o1, t_object o2 where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.start_object_id = o1.object_id and o1.Classifier = o2.Object_ID) union -- find all physical items without allocated elements select o.stereotype as "Stereotype PI", o.name as "Physical Item", null, null from t_object o where (o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalSystem" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalUser" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalEnvironment" or o.stereotype = "SAF_PhysicalExternalSystem") and o.object_id not in (SELECT distinct o2.object_id from t_connector c, t_object o1, t_object o2 where c.stereotype = 'allocate' and c.end_object_id = o1.object_id and o1.pdata1 = o2.ea_guid)
